s:2126:"<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p>The quote that sits below the recent work module on the front page below the main content.</p>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/camper/camper.png" alt="Camper" /></p>
<h2>Steps to recreate this layout</h2>
<p>This item is a custom html module published to the grid17 module. </p>
<p>The background colour used for this row is one of the row styles that can be assigned by row via the template settings. See below for more details.</p>
<p><strong> Module Manager </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to the module manager in your Joomla administrator via extensions &gt; Module Manager</li>
<li>Click new</li>
<li>Select the custom html type module</li>
<li>Copy the markup displayed below into the text area of the custom module.</li>
<li>Assign the module to a module position (sidebar2).</li>
<li>Ensure the module is published</li>
<li>Give the module a title</li>
<li>Set the module title to be hidden</li>
<li>Save your new module.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Markup used in the module</h2>
<pre>&lt;blockquote&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Cras nec lorem eget ligula varius aliquet at et mi.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/blockquote&gt;
    &lt;p style="text-align: right;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;A Happy Camper&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</pre>
<h2>Row Styles set in the template</h2>
<p>The background colour used for this row is determined by the template and can be found in the theme panel in the template administrator.</p>
<p>The row style is applied to a row of modules grouped by their respective rows.</p>
<p>Top row - top1,top2,top3,top4
Banner row - banner
Grid1 row - grid1,grid2,grid3,grid4
Grid2 row - grid5,grid6,grid7,grid8
Grid3 row - grid9,grid10,grid11,grid12
Grid4 row - grid13,grid14,grid15,grid16
Grid5 row - grid17,grid18,grid19,grid20
Grid6 row - grid21,grid22,grid23,grid24
Bottom row - bottom1,bottom2,bottom3,bottom4,bottom5,bottom6
Top row - top1,top2,top3,top4</p>
